$ Registry: HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\shell

{ Open cmd.exe here #open-cmd-exe-here

  The following simple batch file installs a *shortcut (context) menu* on directories that open → Windows/cmd-exe[cmd.exe] with the current directory-path
  set to the directory on which the context menu was executed.

  gh|about-Windows-Registry|/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Classes/Directory/shell/open-cmd.exe-here.bat||

  Compare with → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT/star/shell#open-exec-for-file[Opening any file with a specific application]

}
